.Dd December 16, 2010
.Dt __ARRAYCOUNT 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm __arraycount
.Nd macro for statically allocated arrays
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/cdefs.h
.Ft size_t
.Fn __arraycount x
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn __arraycount
macro returns the number of elements in a statically allocated buffer.
.Sh EXAMPLES
The following example demonstrates a typical usage of
.Fn __arraycount :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
uint8_t buf[BUFSIZE];
size_t i;

\&...

for (i = 0; i < __arraycount(buf); i++)
	\&...
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cdefs 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn __arraycount
macro first appeared in
.Nx 4.0 .
